Class ListDataElement<E>

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    de.esoco.lib.model.DataModel<E>, de.esoco.lib.property.HasProperties, de.esoco.lib.property.MutableProperties, java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Iterable<E>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    DataElementList, DateListDataElement, QueryResultElement, StringListDataElement

    public abstract class ListDataElement<E>
extends DataElement<E>
implements de.esoco.lib.model.DataModel<E>
    A base class for data elements that store a list of elements. The generic type E designates the type of the list elements. A subclass must implement the method getList() to return the list of values. The standard data element methods updateValue(Object) and getValue() are overridden to throw a runtime exception. Access to the list data must be done through the corresponding methods like getElement(int).

    Serialized Form

      • copyValue

        protected void copyValue(DataElement<E> aCopy)
        Copies the value of this data element into another data element of the same type. This is used by the DataElement.copy(CopyMode, PropertyName...) method and by default uses DataElement.updateValue(Object) to set the value in the target element. Subclasses that don't support updating the value (e.g. because they manage a collection) need to override this method and implement the copying as needed. They can assume that the target object is of exactly the same type as their own.
        Overrides:
        copyValue in class DataElement<E>
        Parameters:
        aCopy - The copied data element to copy the value into
